1. Definitions
   1.1. "Company" means WhatsYourWhy, Inc.
   1.2. "Licensed Work" means the Sentinel codebase, associated configuration,
        documentation, and any derivative works that include or are based on
        the Sentinel source files.
   1.3. "Non-Commercial Use" means use by an individual or organization
        solely for personal experimentation, academic research, security
        review, community contributions, or small-scale internal evaluations
        with no revenue-generating or customer-facing outcomes.
   1.4. "Commercial Use" means (a) operating the Licensed Work in production
        to provide alerts, insights, or derivative services that support a
        revenue-generating business or paid engagement, (b) offering the
        Licensed Work or a substantial portion thereof as a managed or hosted
        service, including software-as-a-service or agent-as-a-service
        offerings, or (c) embedding the Licensed Work in a commercial product
        or internal workflow whose primary purpose is to deliver commercial
        value to third parties.
   1.5. "Contribution" means any change submitted to the Company for
        inclusion in the Licensed Work.

2. License Grant
   2.1. Subject to the terms below, Company grants you a worldwide,
        royalty-free, non-exclusive, non-transferable license to use, copy,
        modify, build upon, and redistribute the Licensed Work for
        Non-Commercial Use.
   2.2. You may run the Licensed Work in production solely to validate fit,
        load test, or evaluate functionality for up to three internal users,
        so long as no data or insights produced by the Licensed Work are sold,
        bartered, or incorporated into a revenue-producing workflow.

3. Commercial Use
   3.1. Commercial Use of the Licensed Work requires a separate written
        agreement with Company. Contact the maintainers to obtain a commercial
        license tailored to your deployment or SaaS model.
   3.2. Absent such an agreement, you shall not:
        (a) Provide or resell alerts, insights, or reports generated by the
            Licensed Work as part of a paid service;
        (b) Offer Sentinel, in whole or in part, as a hosted or managed
            capability to third parties;
        (c) Incorporate Sentinel into a commercial product, revenue workflow,
            or fee-based integration; or
        (d) Circumvent these restrictions via subsidiaries, contractors, or
            shared-service organizations.

4. Redistribution Requirements
   4.1. Any redistribution must include this license text and attribution to
        the Company.
   4.2. If you publish modifications for Non-Commercial Use, you must clearly
        document your changes and retain references to this license.
   4.3. You may not remove or alter copyright, trademark, or attribution
        notices.

5. Contributions
